<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>FileZipper</title>

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style1.css">
</head>

<body>


    <nav>
        <h1>File Zipper</h1>
        <a href="/home"><span class="material-icons">home</span> Home</a>
        <a href="/home"><span class="material-icons">
                people
            </span> About Us</a>
        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huffman_coding"><span class="material-icons">
                contact_support
            </span> Help</a>
    </nav>
    <div id="land">

        <main>
            <% if(filesize!='' ){%>

                <h3 id="alert"><i class="material-icons">warning</i> Sorry the file size was greater than 20 MB. File
                    size was : <%= filesize %> B
                </h3>
                <% }%>
                    <h2>Create ZIP File</h2>
                    <p>With this online ZIP converter you can compress your files and create a ZIP archive. Reduce file
                        size
                        and
                        save bandwidth with ZIP compression.</p>
                    <div id="back">
                        <form action="/home" method="post">
                            <label for="choice">Choose an appropriate file format -- (Accepted file types .pdf, .txt) --
                            </label>
                            <br>
                            <select id="choice" name="choice" required>
                                <option name="opt" value="opt" disabled selected>-Select an option-</option>
                                <option name="pdf" value="pdf">PDF
                                </option>
                                <option name="text" value="text">Text</option>

                            </select>
                            <button id="ok">OK</button>
                        </form>
                    </div>

        </main>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom">
        <h3>What is a ZIP file?</h3>
        <p>
            ZIP files are also known as "archive" files. They use lossless compression to reduce the file size
            of
            the
            files contained inside the ZIP.
            Thus, the ZIP file functions as a folder that groups files and uses compression to make it easier to
            store,
            send, and share their content.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom">
        <h3>
            How to compress to ZIP?
        </h3>
        <p>
            1. Upload your files. They can be images, videos, documents or even a mix.
            Click on "Start" to begin with the ZIP compression.<br>
            2. Click on "Start" to begin with the ZIP compression.
        </p>
    </div>
</body>

</html>